lenders.name: Kangaroo Katy's LLC
lenders.loan_because:
Kangaroo Katy’s will be an indoor bounce house in Cottage Grove,  WI, where families can celebrate birthdays, and kids and toddlers can come inside to play. Due to Wisconsin’s unpredictable weather, families such as mine are constantly looking for inexpensive ways to entertain their kids and provide them with fun ways to get exercise when going outside and running is not an option.
Kangaroo Katy’s will be different from other indoor play places because we will only offer healthy snack options and we will beat our competitors’ prices by having reduced rates Wednesdays. We will also offer drop of options for princeton Club Express Members and have a respite/drop off evening available to our special needs population, as well as sensory friendly equipment.
I am a teacher and mother of three children. Teaching has not provided the financial security that I need to bring my family into the future. I am turning my dreams into a reality by starting my own business. This business has huge potential for profit; one of my competitors grossed 150,000 in 2013.
The only thing standing in my way from starting this business is money. I will use this loan to purchase the play equipment, construct the building to suit, and secure my lease.
lenders.occupational_info:
I have spent the last eleven year in the Education profession in Minnesota and Wisconsin. Kids are my passion! I have raised three kids of my own. My eldest has global developmental delays, my middle son has Type One Diabetes, and my youngest is suffering from the effects of divorce. Due to my kids’ varying health needs, I have had to become an expert in health and wellness. My diabetic son needs regular exercise to control his diabetes. This business can provide him with exercise his body needs!
Not only has raising my own kids been educational, but I have gained expertise so to speak in keeping kids safe and providing them with exercise throughout my teaching career. I was trained to teach Physical Education classes to elementary age children and have taught quite a few classes or PE. I also have plenty of experience supervising recess, recreational field trips, and outdoor fun days.
Four years ago we went to Jumpin’ Janes in Dubuque, Iowa. I fell in love with the concept of a Bounce House. Not only did I have an enjoyable experience as an adult, but my children were out of their mind happy. It was then that a seed was planted in my mind and heart and I began to be open to the idea stepping away from my teaching job to begin my own business.
After being divorced for two years and watching the needs of my kids change, I decided to take the leap and leave the education field to start my own business. Since then, I have been mentored by three different Bounce Houses. Monkey Joe’s in Waukesha, Jumpin’ Janes in Dubuque, Iowa, and  former owner of Bouncy Town U.S.A. in Windsor. I have an entrepreneurial spirit and see myself as a life long learner. Currently, I am reading financial a book by author Orrin Woodward and I subscribe to Entrepreneur Magazine. I am also going to start taking business classs at Waukesha Technical College. I will continue to teach myself about the business to ensure I have a healthy and sustainable business.
My kids are my life! Everything I do, I do for them. I have had periods where I have cut back my hours at work and other years where I have worked full time. My kids are growing up before my eyes. Now is the time to step back and lead my family in the future I want. I want financial freedom and flexibility to be home with my kids. Owning my own business is the only way for me to be there for my children and provide a financially stable future for them.
